1
00:00:08,216 --> 00:00:12,929
<i>If you are ever hurt</i>

2
00:00:13,680 --> 00:00:18,935
<i>And find yourself discouraged</i>

3
00:00:19,019 --> 00:00:24,107
<i>I will always be by your side</i>

4
00:00:24,691 --> 00:00:27,235
<i>To hold you up by your shoulders</i>

5
00:00:27,318 --> 00:00:29,029
What was that song again?

6
00:00:30,447 --> 00:00:32,782
So, what could it be?

7
00:00:33,700 --> 00:00:35,410
Oh, I got it!

8
00:00:36,077 --> 00:00:37,287
Yes?

9
00:00:37,370 --> 00:00:38,496
"Tomorrow"!

10
00:00:39,998 --> 00:00:42,250
-Wrong!
-Stop that!

11
00:00:42,333 --> 00:00:44,335
Hey, that's my phone!

12
00:00:44,419 --> 00:00:46,004
Why are you filming?

13
00:00:46,504 --> 00:00:49,549
<i>Carrying the hopes…</i>

14
00:00:49,632 --> 00:00:52,302
Come on, ten days left! Go, go!

15
00:00:53,303 --> 00:00:54,262
Harder!

16
00:00:54,345 --> 00:00:56,347
-Go, Nakaji!
-You're doing great!

17
00:00:56,431 --> 00:00:57,474
Oh, man.

18
00:00:57,557 --> 00:00:59,184
All right, let's go!

19
00:01:00,226 --> 00:01:02,437
Seiichi, want a drink? Here!

20
00:01:04,355 --> 00:01:07,358
Check the breakouts, forecheck,
and backcheck with your line.

21
00:01:07,442 --> 00:01:08,902
Got it.

22
00:01:08,985 --> 00:01:10,361
Okay, good work, everyone.

23
00:01:10,445 --> 00:01:12,030
That's all for practice today.

24
00:01:12,113 --> 00:01:13,490
Seio! One, two, three!

25
00:01:14,824 --> 00:01:16,951
-Have another bowl, okay?
-Seriously?

26
00:01:17,035 --> 00:01:19,370
The balance and quantity
of carbs and protein is--

27
00:01:19,454 --> 00:01:21,331
Oh, shut up already.

28
00:01:21,414 --> 00:01:24,209
Weren't you gonna take
Arata's starting spot before graduation?

29
00:01:24,292 --> 00:01:26,127
Of course I am! Definitely.

30
00:01:26,795 --> 00:01:28,171
I'm looking forward to it.

31
00:01:28,671 --> 00:01:31,716
Man, this guy doesn't feel
threatened at all.

32
00:01:32,300 --> 00:01:35,929
Hey, Arata. You're coming
to the mixer this time, aren't you?

33
00:01:37,055 --> 00:01:39,015
Um, well…

34
00:01:39,099 --> 00:01:41,810
Come on, I'm begging you. Please come.

35
00:01:41,893 --> 00:01:45,063
-The girls would eagerly join if you came.
-Yeah.

36
00:01:45,146 --> 00:01:46,731
We're up against pageant girls.

37
00:01:46,815 --> 00:01:47,690
That's right.

38
00:01:47,774 --> 00:01:49,442
That cheerleader's coming too.

39
00:01:49,526 --> 00:01:50,860
-She's super cute.
-Yeah.

40
00:01:50,944 --> 00:01:52,362
-Seriously.
-It'll be awesome.

41
00:01:52,445 --> 00:01:54,322
Oh, Ryu. You're coming too.

42
00:01:54,405 --> 00:01:55,949
I never said I was going.

43
00:01:56,032 --> 00:01:57,367
Why not? Come on.

44
00:02:03,665 --> 00:02:05,375
That was a foul just now!

45
00:02:12,507 --> 00:02:15,385
Hey, Arata!

46
00:02:15,885 --> 00:02:17,387
What are you doing?

47
00:02:18,012 --> 00:02:19,097
What is it?

48
00:02:19,180 --> 00:02:21,474
-Why are you making that face?
-What?

49
00:02:21,975 --> 00:02:23,935
Hello, this is Narutaki.

50
00:02:24,018 --> 00:02:24,853
Mm-hmm?

51
00:02:24,936 --> 00:02:26,729
-Having love trouble?
-Nah.

52
00:02:27,689 --> 00:02:28,648
Get off me!

53
00:02:28,731 --> 00:02:29,774
Ryu!

54
00:02:31,526 --> 00:02:33,695
Ryu! Arata!

55
00:02:33,778 --> 00:02:35,864
Arata, are your legs holding up?

56
00:02:35,947 --> 00:02:37,907
-I've got energy to spare.
-Okay.

57
00:02:38,491 --> 00:02:41,035
-Did someone ask you out again?
-Come on.

58
00:02:41,119 --> 00:02:43,913
-You're so popular!
-What? Jeez, stop it.

59
00:02:43,997 --> 00:02:45,373
SEIO UNIV. 3
AODAI UNIV. 3

60
00:02:56,009 --> 00:02:57,969
I know someone who's always liked you.

61
00:02:58,469 --> 00:02:59,345
Who?

62
00:03:01,764 --> 00:03:02,640
Me.

63
00:03:03,641 --> 00:03:04,475
Huh?

64
00:03:19,782 --> 00:03:20,950
Shoot!

65
00:03:23,703 --> 00:03:24,829
I have feelings…

66
00:03:28,875 --> 00:03:29,918
for you.

67
00:03:30,793 --> 00:03:32,420
SEIO UNIV. 4
AODAI UNIV. 3

68
00:04:13,336 --> 00:04:18,216
SEIICHI: WHERE ARE YOU?
PLEASE REPLY. NO ONE BLAMES YOU.

69
00:04:19,133 --> 00:04:22,262
You said you were friends!
Did you lie to your father? Wait, Lukas!

70
00:04:22,345 --> 00:04:25,848
I knew this would happen!
That's why I had to lie!

71
00:04:28,184 --> 00:04:29,269
Stop it!

72
00:04:29,352 --> 00:04:32,063
It's bad for the family
that my son is gay!

73
00:04:32,146 --> 00:04:34,732
We can't even go to church!

74
00:04:34,816 --> 00:04:37,860
-You only care about yourself, Dad!
-We're leaving.

75
00:04:37,944 --> 00:04:39,904
I'd rather die if I can't be with him!

76
00:04:39,988 --> 00:04:41,364
God will not forgive you!

77
00:04:41,447 --> 00:04:42,824
Damn the church!

78
00:04:42,907 --> 00:04:46,202
Hey, I got one for you too, Ryu.

79
00:04:46,703 --> 00:04:47,954
Come with me.

80
00:04:48,663 --> 00:04:49,497
What is it?

81
00:04:50,123 --> 00:04:51,249
A boxing match ticket.

82
00:04:52,083 --> 00:04:54,043
Sure, I'll go with you.

83
00:04:54,544 --> 00:04:55,628
But why boxing?

84
00:04:56,879 --> 00:05:00,967
There's a competition coming up at school.
Winning could really open doors for me.

85
00:05:01,050 --> 00:05:03,386
And my theme is

86
00:05:04,262 --> 00:05:05,763
fists and beauty.

87
00:05:08,141 --> 00:05:09,392
Fists?

88
00:05:09,475 --> 00:05:10,893
And beauty.

89
00:05:11,394 --> 00:05:12,228
And beauty.

90
00:05:13,146 --> 00:05:15,231
But hey, is this really okay?

91
00:05:15,315 --> 00:05:16,441
What is?

92
00:05:16,524 --> 00:05:20,403
Ice hockey.
You're missing so much practice.

93
00:05:21,070 --> 00:05:23,156
I've been playing since middle school.

94
00:05:24,115 --> 00:05:26,492
I need to refresh myself once in a while.

95
00:05:28,369 --> 00:05:31,831
You call this refreshing?
All you're doing is lazing around.

96
00:05:32,332 --> 00:05:35,835
Lazing around overseas.
That's refreshing to me.

97
00:05:37,045 --> 00:05:40,548
You'll get flabby before you know it.
Especially your upper arms.

98
00:05:41,132 --> 00:05:42,717
Flabby?

99
00:05:56,272 --> 00:05:58,733
-Cheers!
-Cheers.

100
00:05:59,233 --> 00:06:00,151
Yeah.

101
00:06:17,460 --> 00:06:21,297
That's true.
Stories definitely do bring in money.

102
00:06:21,381 --> 00:06:22,590
I'm glad you're here.

103
00:06:25,843 --> 00:06:28,471
Was the hotel to your liking?

104
00:06:29,597 --> 00:06:30,723
Yes.

105
00:06:33,226 --> 00:06:34,644
Oh, here.

106
00:06:37,605 --> 00:06:39,148
Your advance payment.

107
00:06:45,071 --> 00:06:48,908
I trust you. Do a good job, okay?

108
00:06:49,492 --> 00:06:50,535
Yes, sir.

109
00:07:10,847 --> 00:07:12,473
-I'll go get a drink.
-Sure.

110
00:07:38,833 --> 00:07:39,667
Here.

111
00:07:41,502 --> 00:07:42,837
-So, Layla was saying…
-Yeah?

112
00:07:42,920 --> 00:07:45,590
She says you should check out her work.

113
00:07:46,507 --> 00:07:47,341
Check them out?

114
00:07:48,009 --> 00:07:50,887
Yeah, she said
you should take a good look.

115
00:07:50,970 --> 00:07:54,640
Layla makes sculptures,
using human sin as her theme.

116
00:07:54,724 --> 00:07:56,058
I see.

117
00:08:02,815 --> 00:08:05,985
They're being displayed
at a church near my place.

118
00:08:06,068 --> 00:08:09,071
Wanna drop by together
before the boxing match?

119
00:08:09,572 --> 00:08:11,449
Yeah, sounds good.

120
00:08:30,009 --> 00:08:33,721
<i>At the time, I couldn't say anything.</i>

121
00:08:35,264 --> 00:08:36,682
<i>I couldn't move.</i>

122
00:08:37,683 --> 00:08:41,812
<i>Learning how I truly felt</i>

123
00:08:42,563 --> 00:08:43,523
<i>scared me.</i>

124
00:08:43,606 --> 00:08:46,234
Hey, Arata!

125
00:08:46,317 --> 00:08:47,568
What are you doing?

126
00:08:48,069 --> 00:08:49,362
What is it?

127
00:08:49,445 --> 00:08:51,697
-Why are you making that face?
-What?

128
00:08:52,198 --> 00:08:54,200
Hello, this is Narutaki.

129
00:08:54,283 --> 00:08:55,117
Mm-hmm?

130
00:08:55,201 --> 00:08:57,578
-Having love trouble?
-Nah.

131
00:09:01,165 --> 00:09:02,500
By the way, that mixer…

132
00:09:03,751 --> 00:09:04,710
Are you going?

133
00:09:04,794 --> 00:09:08,047
Well, I'm not great
with that kind of stuff.

134
00:09:08,548 --> 00:09:09,715
Are you?

135
00:09:10,800 --> 00:09:12,927
-No.
-I see.

136
00:09:13,427 --> 00:09:14,512
Oh.

137
00:09:14,595 --> 00:09:17,348
-I know! Did someone ask you out again?
-Come on.

138
00:09:17,431 --> 00:09:19,976
-You're so popular!
-Jeez, stop it.

139
00:09:25,690 --> 00:09:27,650
-You know what?
-What?

140
00:09:28,901 --> 00:09:30,820
I know someone who's always liked you.

141
00:09:30,903 --> 00:09:32,280
Who?

142
00:09:34,740 --> 00:09:35,658
Me.

143
00:09:37,201 --> 00:09:38,160
Huh?

144
00:09:43,332 --> 00:09:44,417
Like I said…

145
00:09:49,880 --> 00:09:51,132
I have feelings…

146
00:09:53,676 --> 00:09:54,719
for you.

147
00:10:04,395 --> 00:10:05,688
Shocking, isn't it?

148
00:10:24,040 --> 00:10:26,250
Sorry to drop this on you before a match.

149
00:10:26,876 --> 00:10:27,752
It's fine.

150
00:10:32,798 --> 00:10:36,010
It's not like I want
an answer or anything.

151
00:10:40,681 --> 00:10:41,932
I just wanted you…

152
00:10:44,018 --> 00:10:47,772
to know how I feel.

153
00:10:51,317 --> 00:10:52,818
That alone…

154
00:10:55,237 --> 00:10:57,948
is enough to change my world.

155
00:11:05,665 --> 00:11:06,666
Well…

156
00:11:07,375 --> 00:11:09,710
Good night, then.

157
00:11:10,920 --> 00:11:11,837
Yeah.

158
00:11:14,423 --> 00:11:15,466
<i>You know what?</i>

159
00:11:17,593 --> 00:11:19,762
<i>I know someone who's always liked you.</i>

160
00:11:19,845 --> 00:11:20,930
<i>Who?</i>

161
00:11:21,972 --> 00:11:22,973
<i>Me.</i>

162
00:13:42,154 --> 00:13:43,197
I…

163
00:13:45,366 --> 00:13:46,492
I…

164
00:13:52,248 --> 00:13:53,707
I cast aside…

165
00:13:56,335 --> 00:13:57,878
his feelings.

166
00:14:04,593 --> 00:14:05,636
I'm…

167
00:14:08,639 --> 00:14:12,226
I'm… the worst.

168
00:14:19,567 --> 00:14:20,693
I was scared.

169
00:14:24,238 --> 00:14:26,198
Scared of being liked.

170
00:14:29,827 --> 00:14:31,787
I'm sorry.

171
00:14:32,788 --> 00:14:36,458
I'm sorry.

172
00:14:38,043 --> 00:14:40,838
I'm sorry.

173
00:14:49,763 --> 00:14:50,764
Dammit.

174
00:14:51,849 --> 00:14:53,893
Why is it always me? Why?

175
00:14:54,393 --> 00:14:55,436
Wait!

176
00:14:56,854 --> 00:14:58,272
Hey, wait!

177
00:15:46,153 --> 00:15:47,696
I get it.

178
00:16:03,629 --> 00:16:04,630
I'm sorry.

179
00:16:05,673 --> 00:16:07,466
Your feelings…

180
00:16:09,218 --> 00:16:10,594
And your life…

181
00:16:11,136 --> 00:16:12,596
I ruined all of it.

182
00:16:14,056 --> 00:16:15,140
Hey!

183
00:16:16,600 --> 00:16:17,601
Hey!

184
00:16:25,275 --> 00:16:27,528
Arata, I'm sorry.

185
00:16:32,533 --> 00:16:35,244
Ryu!

186
00:16:35,327 --> 00:16:37,788
Oh, thank goodness.

187
00:16:39,873 --> 00:16:40,916
Did…

188
00:16:43,836 --> 00:16:45,838
Did somebody save me?

189
00:16:47,881 --> 00:16:48,924
Yeah.

190
00:16:49,008 --> 00:16:54,054
You were found unconscious
with another man.

191
00:16:54,138 --> 00:16:58,434
But it looks like
he slipped out of the hospital room.

192
00:17:01,395 --> 00:17:02,771
I see.

193
00:17:47,816 --> 00:17:50,819
<i>So, how are you feeling?</i>

194
00:17:51,612 --> 00:17:52,738
Same as always.

195
00:17:53,405 --> 00:17:54,865
<i>Huh? What are you doing?</i>

196
00:17:56,241 --> 00:17:58,202
Nothing.

197
00:17:59,578 --> 00:18:01,371
<i>You're reading manga again.</i>

198
00:18:03,248 --> 00:18:05,167
Shut up.

199
00:18:06,585 --> 00:18:09,379
<i>You really love that stuff, don't you?</i>

200
00:18:11,006 --> 00:18:12,341
Is that so wrong?

201
00:18:15,344 --> 00:18:17,054
<i>So, how's Berlin?</i>

202
00:18:27,564 --> 00:18:28,607
Just normal.

203
00:18:47,709 --> 00:18:49,211
Do you have a minute?

204
00:18:54,758 --> 00:18:56,051
Um…

205
00:18:56,844 --> 00:18:59,805
I'm sorry I've been keeping quiet.

206
00:19:02,224 --> 00:19:04,977
I put you through all this worry too.

207
00:19:07,187 --> 00:19:08,230
It's fine.

208
00:19:10,065 --> 00:19:11,441
I'll be honest.

209
00:19:15,571 --> 00:19:16,947
I ran away.

210
00:19:18,282 --> 00:19:19,324
From Japan.

211
00:19:21,660 --> 00:19:22,703
What?

212
00:19:32,588 --> 00:19:33,589
Here.

213
00:19:40,470 --> 00:19:41,930
Can I watch it?

214
00:19:42,014 --> 00:19:43,015
Yeah.

215
00:19:51,607 --> 00:19:52,733
I have feelings…

216
00:19:56,612 --> 00:19:57,696
for you.

217
00:20:00,949 --> 00:20:01,992
What?

218
00:20:13,837 --> 00:20:15,130
Shocking, isn't it?

219
00:20:33,857 --> 00:20:34,983
What's wrong?

220
00:20:37,027 --> 00:20:38,070
Nothing.

221
00:20:51,041 --> 00:20:52,084
Hello?

222
00:20:52,167 --> 00:20:55,671
<i>Hi. Uh, are you alone right now?</i>

223
00:20:55,754 --> 00:20:58,340
Yeah. I think Seiichi's taking a bath.

224
00:20:58,840 --> 00:20:59,800
<i>Oh.</i>

225
00:21:00,467 --> 00:21:02,552
<i>Um, what about Arata?</i>

226
00:21:04,638 --> 00:21:05,681
Huh?

227
00:21:05,764 --> 00:21:11,144
<i>Oh, uh, you were walking with him</i>
<i>by the riverside earlier, right?</i>

228
00:21:14,106 --> 00:21:15,190
So what?

229
00:21:15,732 --> 00:21:20,195
<i>Oh, well, um…</i>

230
00:21:21,029 --> 00:21:24,616
<i>I was wondering if he asked you out.</i>

231
00:21:25,575 --> 00:21:26,618
What?

232
00:21:27,202 --> 00:21:29,997
<i>I mean, it just had that vibe.</i>

233
00:21:30,080 --> 00:21:34,960
<i>You know, I kind of had a hunch</i>
<i>that maybe Arata swings that way.</i>

234
00:21:37,087 --> 00:21:39,381
<i>So, um…</i>

235
00:21:41,049 --> 00:21:42,426
<i>Are you guys dating?</i>

236
00:21:42,926 --> 00:21:44,803
No, obviously not.

237
00:21:45,762 --> 00:21:48,849
<i>Sorry. I didn't mean it in a weird way.</i>

238
00:21:48,932 --> 00:21:52,644
<i>I'm not homophobic or anything,</i>
<i>so it's totally okay with me.</i>

239
00:21:54,187 --> 00:21:55,439
Well, you know…

240
00:21:57,733 --> 00:21:58,608
You know, it's…

241
00:21:58,692 --> 00:22:03,488
<i>Oh, uh… I get it.</i>
<i>You don't swing that way, right?</i>

242
00:22:04,614 --> 00:22:07,993
<i>Um, well… Sorry about this, really.</i>

243
00:22:08,577 --> 00:22:10,162
-<i>Bye, then.</i>
-No, I…

244
00:22:21,089 --> 00:22:23,216
I seriously didn't realize.

245
00:22:23,759 --> 00:22:26,219
Sorry I invited you to mixers and stuff.

246
00:22:26,303 --> 00:22:27,721
That was insensitive of me.

247
00:22:27,804 --> 00:22:28,638
Oh, come on!

248
00:22:28,722 --> 00:22:31,600
You were totally using Arata
to get the girls to come.

249
00:22:31,683 --> 00:22:33,685
-That's true!
-We're… You know?

250
00:22:33,769 --> 00:22:36,271
-We're fine with that stuff.
-Totally.

251
00:22:36,355 --> 00:22:37,189
Hi.

252
00:22:38,482 --> 00:22:40,901
-Morning!
-Morning.

253
00:22:52,162 --> 00:22:55,123
Well, I'll head out first.

254
00:22:55,207 --> 00:22:56,708
-Okay.
-See you.

255
00:23:02,631 --> 00:23:06,426
I didn't mean to out him or anything.

256
00:23:07,219 --> 00:23:11,014
But I thought we needed to
accept Arata for who he is.

257
00:23:11,098 --> 00:23:12,849
Accept him?

258
00:23:15,060 --> 00:23:16,395
What's that supposed to mean?

259
00:23:16,478 --> 00:23:19,356
So, this refers to the cerebrum.

260
00:23:19,856 --> 00:23:21,858
Humans were thought to respond to stimuli…

261
00:23:21,942 --> 00:23:24,111
SORRY. I DIDN'T MEAN FOR THAT TO HAPPEN.

262
00:23:24,194 --> 00:23:27,656
This is called behaviorism.

263
00:23:28,240 --> 00:23:33,995
In contrast, Tolman argued
that individuals react differently

264
00:23:34,079 --> 00:23:37,582
when the organism mediates
between stimulus and response.

265
00:23:38,333 --> 00:23:41,378
This is called neo-behaviorism.

266
00:23:41,461 --> 00:23:44,840
With this new theory,
each individual responds differently…

267
00:24:02,524 --> 00:24:03,525
Ryu.

268
00:24:05,444 --> 00:24:06,570
I need to talk to you.

269
00:24:08,822 --> 00:24:10,657
I just got a call.

270
00:24:14,286 --> 00:24:15,829
It's about Arata.

271
00:24:18,790 --> 00:24:20,000
He jumped.

272
00:24:23,628 --> 00:24:24,629
What?

273
00:24:25,547 --> 00:24:27,591
They took him to the hospital.

274
00:24:30,010 --> 00:24:32,179
I don't know the details yet.

275
00:24:38,685 --> 00:24:41,771
You know how we always went
to the public baths with him?

276
00:24:41,855 --> 00:24:42,981
Yeah.

277
00:24:43,064 --> 00:24:45,275
For him, the men's bath is like…

278
00:24:46,985 --> 00:24:48,278
You get what I'm saying?

279
00:24:48,778 --> 00:24:51,406
Yeah, it's like us going
in the women's bath.

280
00:24:51,490 --> 00:24:52,782
Exactly.

281
00:24:52,866 --> 00:24:54,659
-Isn't that crazy?
-Totally.

282
00:24:54,743 --> 00:24:57,370
-Should I give it a shot?
-You'll get caught.

283
00:25:29,653 --> 00:25:32,739
<i>The person you are trying to reach</i>
<i>is unavailable.</i>

284
00:25:32,822 --> 00:25:37,953
<i>Please leave your name and message</i>
<i>after the tone.</i>

285
00:25:40,205 --> 00:25:41,248
I'm sorry.

286
00:25:45,126 --> 00:25:46,211
I'm sorry.

287
00:25:49,256 --> 00:25:50,340
I'm really sorry.

288
00:25:53,260 --> 00:25:54,886
-Arata?
-<i>Hey, Ryu!</i>

289
00:25:55,470 --> 00:25:57,180
<i>Where are you?</i>

290
00:25:57,264 --> 00:25:58,932
<i>The game's about to start!</i>

291
00:26:00,267 --> 00:26:01,518
<i>Hey, do you hear me?</i>

292
00:26:02,018 --> 00:26:04,437
<i>Ryu! Do you hear me?</i>

293
00:26:16,992 --> 00:26:20,579
<i>If, right now</i>

294
00:26:20,662 --> 00:26:25,709
<i>I can be true to my feelings</i>

295
00:26:26,251 --> 00:26:30,463
<i>My admiration</i>

296
00:26:30,547 --> 00:26:34,676
<i>And my love</i>

297
00:26:34,759 --> 00:26:40,974
<i>Will fly to the wide open sky</i>

298
00:26:41,057 --> 00:26:43,935
<i>And shine brightly</i>

299
00:26:44,686 --> 00:26:48,857
<i>I believe in future</i>

300
00:26:48,940 --> 00:26:53,278
<i>I believe</i>

301
00:27:08,418 --> 00:27:11,296
I'M OFF TO SCHOOL.
EAT IT WHEN YOU'RE HUNGRY.

302
00:27:11,379 --> 00:27:12,589
FROM SUMIKO

303
00:27:25,685 --> 00:27:28,229
He's not Japanese. He's Korean.

304
00:27:29,230 --> 00:27:32,984
He's Korean. He's not from this country.

305
00:27:33,068 --> 00:27:36,738
There are signs that he tried to save you.

306
00:27:36,821 --> 00:27:40,575
He is a suspect,
but we don't know his motive.

307
00:27:41,159 --> 00:27:45,413
You said two people were arguing, right?

308
00:27:46,706 --> 00:27:48,625
He won't tell us anything.

309
00:27:49,209 --> 00:27:53,129
He won't tell us anything
about the other person.

310
00:27:53,213 --> 00:27:54,506
We're at a loss.

311
00:28:15,110 --> 00:28:16,111
Hey.

312
00:28:17,696 --> 00:28:18,613
Excuse me.

313
00:28:18,697 --> 00:28:19,698
What?

314
00:28:33,878 --> 00:28:36,423
Are you Japanese?

315
00:28:38,007 --> 00:28:39,008
Yes.

316
00:28:40,009 --> 00:28:41,720
Um…

317
00:28:45,473 --> 00:28:47,559
I know a bit of Japanese.

318
00:28:47,642 --> 00:28:49,686
Oh, I see.

319
00:28:51,271 --> 00:28:53,648
Thank you for saving me.

320
00:28:58,862 --> 00:28:59,946
It's nothing.

321
00:29:00,655 --> 00:29:01,656
Bye.

322
00:29:06,536 --> 00:29:07,454
Wait, um…

323
00:29:07,954 --> 00:29:11,332
Hold on. Hey.

324
00:29:11,416 --> 00:29:13,376
Um, the confession booth.

325
00:29:14,794 --> 00:29:16,045
At the church.

326
00:29:16,796 --> 00:29:20,800
You were on the other side, weren't you?

327
00:29:28,975 --> 00:29:31,728
That's none of your business. Got it?

328
00:29:31,811 --> 00:29:34,898
Well, that's true, but…

329
00:29:40,779 --> 00:29:43,031
What are you hoping for?

330
00:29:43,531 --> 00:29:46,034
-Hoping for?
-Yeah.

331
00:29:46,117 --> 00:29:48,286
What do you mean?

332
00:29:54,626 --> 00:29:58,379
Your sins have nothing to do with me.

333
00:30:00,298 --> 00:30:03,676
You're not even Christian, are you?

334
00:30:04,761 --> 00:30:05,762
Huh?

335
00:30:06,346 --> 00:30:07,347
I mean, um…

336
00:30:08,556 --> 00:30:11,601
The side you were sitting
is where the priest sits.

337
00:30:12,894 --> 00:30:13,978
Uh…

338
00:30:17,649 --> 00:30:20,401
Like I said, it's none of your business.

339
00:30:20,485 --> 00:30:21,486
Got it?

340
00:30:29,953 --> 00:30:33,915
Wait, did I do something to you?

341
00:30:39,796 --> 00:30:41,631
You didn't do anything.

342
00:30:42,382 --> 00:30:43,466
And neither did I.

343
00:30:44,551 --> 00:30:47,262
That's why I don't need your thanks.

344
00:30:51,975 --> 00:30:54,143
We just crossed paths in this city.

345
00:30:54,644 --> 00:30:57,730
We won't ever meet again, right?

346
00:31:09,450 --> 00:31:10,827
What a pathetic guy.

347
00:31:20,253 --> 00:31:22,171
-I'm back.
-Hey.

348
00:31:24,215 --> 00:31:26,050
-Sorry I left this.
-Hmm?

349
00:31:26,551 --> 00:31:30,430
That's totally fine. Where did you go?

350
00:31:32,181 --> 00:31:34,893
Hey, don't force yourself.

351
00:31:34,976 --> 00:31:37,687
You won't have room for dinner.

352
00:31:37,770 --> 00:31:40,356
It's okay. I can eat endlessly.

353
00:31:49,198 --> 00:31:50,742
I went to the police.

354
00:31:55,747 --> 00:31:58,374
I met the guy who saved me from the fire.

355
00:31:59,334 --> 00:32:01,794
Oh? What was he like?

356
00:32:04,756 --> 00:32:06,591
I'm not really sure.

357
00:32:07,926 --> 00:32:11,095
But he's totally different from me.

358
00:32:12,597 --> 00:32:13,431
I guess.

359
00:32:13,514 --> 00:32:16,059
-Oh?
-Yeah.

360
00:32:22,190 --> 00:32:23,399
I'll help.

361
00:32:23,483 --> 00:32:24,317
Okay.

362
00:32:25,234 --> 00:32:27,570
Thanks. In that case…

363
00:32:28,488 --> 00:32:30,698
Can you peel these?

364
00:32:32,617 --> 00:32:34,243
-Sure.
-Thank you.

365
00:32:42,585 --> 00:32:47,215
Well, we'll go watch
the boxing match tomorrow.

366
00:32:47,298 --> 00:32:50,426
Let's relieve our stress like, "Aaah!"

367
00:32:50,510 --> 00:32:52,595
You know, "Aaah!"

368
00:32:53,429 --> 00:32:55,890
-Go "Aaah"?
-Yeah, exactly.

369
00:32:56,557 --> 00:33:01,729
When I watched your ice hockey match
back in high school,

370
00:33:01,813 --> 00:33:06,150
you'd charge straight at
your opponents like, "Wham!"

371
00:33:06,234 --> 00:33:08,903
And I was like, "Aaah!"

372
00:33:09,404 --> 00:33:13,491
You took down huge guys
even though you weren't that buff.

373
00:33:13,574 --> 00:33:16,703
Watching you gave me courage.

374
00:33:59,620 --> 00:34:00,913
Ryu, over here.

375
00:34:12,717 --> 00:34:14,010
Excuse me.

376
00:34:50,421 --> 00:34:52,965
Hwang Johan!

377
00:34:54,967 --> 00:34:55,968
Huh?

378
00:34:57,804 --> 00:35:00,264
-Hmm?
-Nothing.

379
00:35:10,608 --> 00:35:15,279
<i>The moment I stepped into the ring,</i>
<i>I tried not to look at the crowd.</i>

380
00:35:16,072 --> 00:35:18,699
<i>I had a feeling</i>
<i>that everything was about to begin.</i>

381
00:35:19,450 --> 00:35:24,038
<i>The joy, the pain, and the suffering.</i>

382
00:35:24,122 --> 00:35:26,124
Don't get dragged into his rhythm.

383
00:35:26,207 --> 00:35:28,417
Stick to your boxing style, got it?

384
00:35:28,501 --> 00:35:29,710
Let's do this!

385
00:35:37,135 --> 00:35:39,595
Hwang Johan…

386
00:35:40,429 --> 00:35:44,517
<i>On this day, our story begins.</i>

387
00:37:55,523 --> 00:37:58,442
Subtitle translation by: Remi Miura
